DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Total Nucleated Cell Count Per Kilogram Bone Marrow Cell Dose Present Decimal Place Integer Outcome Laboratory Procedure Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A value regarding a laboratory procedure from bone marrow that indicates the total nucleated cells per kilogram.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Total Nucleated Cell Count Per Kilogram Bone Marrow Cell Dose Present
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting._Pertaining to an entirety or whole, also constituting the full quantity or extent; complete; derived by addition._The determination of the amount of nucleated cells present in a sample._For each, generally denoting a ratio._A basic SI unit of mass. It is defined as the mass of an international prototype in the form of a platinum-iridium cylinder kept at Sevres in France. A kilogram is equal to 1,000 grams and 2.204 622 6 pounds._The tissue occupying the spaces of bone. It consists of blood vessel sinuses and a network of hematopoietic cells which give rise to the red cells, white cells, and megakaryocytes._The smallest units of living structure capable of independent existence, composed of a membrane-enclosed mass of protoplasm and containing a nucleus or nucleoid._A quantity of an agent (such as substance or energy) administered, taken, or absorbed at one time._Being or existing in a specified place or at the specified time.
